<html><head><title>Class Issues Lists updated</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Class Issues Lists updated</h3><p>If you're tired of that spell that causes too much agro or constantly being out of mana when other classes are not - check out your class issues list, a fix might just be in the works!<br><br>You can find them by going to the <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq?category.id=Classes">class boards here</a>, clicking your class, and then clicking the "Definition" forum.  The class issues link is always one of the first posts on the board.</div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Mon 22 Nov 2004<br>Link: http://eqvault.ign.com//index.php#3643<br>Printed On: Wed Dec 8 4:26:44 PST 2004<br>©2004 IGN Entertainment</font></span>